#### Specifications

##### ALTERED Core Actions

- Actions Palette Action Definition: An Action called "Actions Palette" in the ALTERED Core System that opens a grid of all of a user's installed Actions, grouped by their parent System.
- Actions Palette Groups: Each group will have the System title as the group title, and the System name as the subtitle. Typing in the search bar in the top will filter the Actions by all of their metadata, including their parent System.
- Actions Palette Shortcuts: Accessing an Action quickly is key, so we will integrate chords/aliases as a way to open them once the Palette is open. This will consist of configuring a command with a string (e.g., "view" for viewing Thoughts), then simply typing it in the Palette search and confirming it with either a space, tab, or any character (this will currently become a constant that we can test, but may become a user preference). When a chord is recognized, the Raycast `navigationTitle` prop will be updated to show a confirmation.

- Capture Thought Action Definition: An Action called "Capture Thought" in the ALTERED Core System that opens a form for creating a Thought. This will be a multi-step Flow, with the first step being an isolated text input, and subsequent steps (we can try to put all in one) for adding an Alias, assigning Datasets, etc.
- Capture Thought AI Inference: Part of the reason for splitting the form across multiple Interfaces is that we want to prefetch and load the most relevant suggestions for the Thought's Attributes, such as the Alias and Datasets.
- Capture Thought File Inclusion: We won't create another Action for uploading files, since Thoughts are the primitive type and files should always be attached to thoughts. There will also be no folders in ALTERED, as we fundamentally use tag-based indexing over filesystem paths. This means that we will only select one file at a time when capturing a Thought (with the exception of the Warp Thoughts Action, which can upload multiple files at once).

- Warp Thoughts Action Definition: An action called "Warp Thought" in the ALTERED Core system that reads from the clipboard and saves any text or files as a Thought to your ALTERED Drafts Dataset. Displays a HUD (achieved by hiding a Raycast toast) with a primary action that opens the submitted Thought.

- "View Thoughts": A Raycast list view. Will include functionality for viewing, archiving, inspecting, and editing thoughts.
- "Create Dataset": An Interface for creating a Dataset.
- "View Datasets": A Raycast list view. Will provide functionality for viewing, inspecting, archiving, and editing Datasets and their Schemas.
- "Switch Brain": A Raycast list view of all of your existing Brains, with the ability to create a new one.

##### ALTERED IO

- "Update Indexed Files": Reads a file or directory, and re-uploads indexed files (based on a UUID filename or hidden metadata property) that have changed (based on the file's hash, metadata, or otherwise)
- "Generate LLMs.txt": Select Thoughts with a query, and copy to clipboard or save to file.
- "Download Filetree": Select various Thoughts, derive an optimal structure based on the Datasets of each Thought, and export as a directory of organized folders.
- "Offload to Disk": Export or backup (all, or a selection of) Thoughts and files to an SSD or local drive (to save on storage costs, edit/use the files, or access without the internet).

##### ALTERED History

- "View History": See all changes and interact with them, with the ability to revert to a certain point.

##### ALTERED Version Control

- "Validation Scopes": Add validation scopes to a specific Dataset or all Thoughts.
- "Validate thoughts": Review thoughts and validate/invalidate them based on a specific scope.

